detaileddescription.para:
This macro is used to declare variables which are used for saving FPU context, and it will store the nessary fpu registers into these variables, it need to be used in a interrupt when in this interrupt fpu registers are used. 


It need to be used together with RESTORE_FPU_CONTEXT
Don't use variable names __fpu_context in your ISR code
If you isr code will use fpu registers, and this interrupt is nested. Then you can do it like this: voideclic_mtip_handler(void)
{
//!!!Interruptisenabledhere!!!
//!!!Higherpriorityinterruptcouldnestit!!!

//Necessaryonlywhenyouneedtousefpuregisters
//inthisisrhandlerfunctions
SAVE_FPU_CONTEXT();

//putyouowninterrupthandlingcodehere

//pairofSAVE_FPU_CONTEXT()
RESTORE_FPU_CONTEXT();
}
